@page "/no-party-binding"
@attribute [Authorize(Policy = PartiesUiAuthorization.ConsumerPolicy)]

@*
    Story 1.4 — fail-closed Consumer data-binding state. An authenticated Consumer whose principal
    carries no single valid party_id binding is diverted HERE by RoleLandingRedirect instead of the /me
    data area. This is NOT a data screen: it renders only static onboarding/error copy and never fetches
    or displays party data (no PII). Gated on the Consumer policy (the unbound user IS an authenticated
    Consumer); enforcement comes from <AuthorizeRouteView> in Routes.razor. The <h1> is the focus target
    for <FocusOnNavigate Selector="h1">. The copy register is plain / reassuring, neutral-info (never
    success-green). Distinct from the role-less "No area assigned" state in RoleLandingRedirect.

    Not yet localized — mirrors the hardcoded-English stub style of the predecessor scaffold pages
    (RoleLandingRedirect's no-area block). Do not introduce IStringLocalizer here; stay consistent with
    the predecessor until the area is localized as a whole.
*@

<h1>We're still setting up your profile</h1>
<p>
    Your account isn't linked to a profile yet. This can take a little while after you first sign in.
    Please contact your administrator or support, and they'll get you set up.
</p>
